{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-3091"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of motorcycles"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "3091"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :motorcycle/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :rider-safety :road-safety :emissions-compliance]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :motorcycle-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MotoAdvisor ⊣ Motorcycle Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for motorcycle manufacturing (frame-welding/
 engine-assembly/final-assembly/test lines producing finished
 motorcycles, scooters, mopeds and electric motorcycles) -- not
 direct welding/assembly/test-bench-equipment control authority and
 not type-approval/safety-certification authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct
 welding/assembly/test-bench-equipment control), permanent
 equipment-actuate block, permanent type-approval/safety-
 certification-authority block (this actor never self-issues an ECE
 R78 brake-system / ECE R40 emissions motorcycle type-approval
 certification), independent equipment verification/registration
 before maintenance scheduling, independent batch verification/
 registration before shipment coordination, independent
 shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own logged
 production quantity, double-schedule guard, product-category
 validation, engine-displacement plausibility validation, and
 weld-defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (frame-weld-defect/brake-safety/emissions-compliance) ALWAYS
 escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is
 the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
